#################
### SimVizMap ###
#################

Spatial visualization from simulation results

This package contains code to create visualizations from econometric
simulations as suggested in Arribas-Bel, Koschinsky and Amaral (2011)

A little tutorial explaining how to use the package to create simulation 
maps is included as a pdf

Authors
=======
Dani Arribas-Bel <daniel.arribas.bel@gmail.com>
Julia Koschinsky <julia.koschinsky@asu.edu>
Pedro V. Amaral <pvmda2@cam.ac.uk>

References
==========
Arribas-Bel, D., Koschinsky, J., Amaral, P. V. (2011) 
"Improving the Multi-Dimensional Comparison of Simulation Results: A Spatial Visualization Approach". Letters in Spatial and Resource Sciences.

Dependencies
============
To use this package, you will need to have installed the following libraries:
    * Numpy
    * Scipy
    * Matplotlib
